body:
Comment 3: 
The printString, printInt, etc. functions are named just so because we want to highlight
the types involved in the type switch. It's ok to assume a reasonably intelligent reader
will understand what is meant.

All other print forms exist in some form. No need to be overly pedantic here: These are
examples, not definitions.  The meaning is clear.
_Status changed to **WorkingAsIntended**._
